# Comms public navigation

## Get started (progressive CTA)

**Get started** in Header resolves to `/onboarding` when Brand Kit is not established, otherwise `/guide/social-media-plan` (First week roadmap). Do **not** retarget Get started at `/brand-kit` once identity exists ‚Äî Brand Kit stays its own top-level link.

Brand Kit is the Comms home base (colours, logo, local number, links). First week (`/guide/social-media-plan`) is the channel roadmap after identity ‚Äî also listed under Learn ‚Üí Guides and the home ‚ÄúWhat‚Äôs next‚Äù CTA.

## Header Learn menu (keep this shape)

Three groups in [`nav-config.ts`](src/components/layout/nav/nav-config.ts) `learnGroups`:

1. **Guides** ‚Äî Comms Resources, The Blueprint, First week (`/guide/social-media-plan`), Strike Guide, Photo Consent (`/guide/photo-consent`)
2. **By channel** ‚Äî Print Guide (`/guide/print`), Union Boards Guide, Website Guide
3. **Libraries** ‚Äî Social Examples, Captions

Do not re-flatten channel guides into a long top-level link bar. Do not promote `/manifesto` into Header (quiet home trust link by design). Do not promote `/install` into Header (muted footer + support/privacy cross-links only ‚Äî see `.cursor/rules/pwa.mdc`).

## Header Tools menu (keep this shape)

Four groups in `nav-config.ts` `toolGroups` (mega-menu columns):

1. **Brand** ‚Äî Logo Builder, Resizer, Document & Slide Generator
2. **Union boards** ‚Äî Board Banner & Trim, Board Notice Maker, Solidarity Posters, QR Board Posters, QR Link Cards
3. **Print** ‚Äî Flyer Maker
4. **Social & web** ‚Äî Graphic Maker, Quote Card, Meeting Backgrounds, Website Template, Alt-Text Assistant

Footer row in the mega-menu: **All tools** ‚Üí `/tools` index. Do not re-flatten Tools into a single ungrouped list. Keep one **Tools ‚ñæ** trigger ‚Äî do not add extra top-level tool links.

## Footer

Include Tools (`/tools`) and Print Guide alongside Blueprint / Examples / Captions / Resources so print-first locals are not chrome-orphaned. Privacy, Accessibility, Support stay in footer. **Install as an app** (`/install`) is a muted text link under the footer blurb ‚Äî not a peer of Privacy/Support in the footer nav row.

## Brand Assets

`/assets` is not a Header top-level item. Link from Brand Kit (`brandKit.assetsLink`). Home Brand Kit card may mention assets in copy; prefer a real route link on Brand Kit.

## Keep out of public chrome

- Operator docs (`docs/guides/SETUP.md`, `DEPLOY.md`)
- Hub modules (use `HubNav`)
- Invented marketing routes (`/about`, `/pricing`, `/blog`) unless product expands
- PWA install guide (`/install`) ‚Äî quiet only; never Learn/Tools/Header

